title: All Girls Garage
subTitle: This mid-engine classic needs to get back on the road; the crew goes through the engine to see if it needs a rebuild, then overhauls the fuel delivery system to get this build over some major hurdles.

title: Car Fix
subTitle: Fuller and Bumpus show what it takes to put a marine-grade LS7 into a classic '85 El Camino. There is a difference between engines built for the road and those built for the water.

title: Street Outlaws
subTitle: With only two list races left in the season, Farmtruck and AZN prepare for racing with some fishing. And, on race night, tempers flare between Doc and Monza.

title: Salvage Hunters: Classic Cars
subTitle: Drew takes the first type of car he owned, and transforms it with a modern-day makeover. He thinks this ex-Royal Mail delivery van could be considered a perfect affordable classic.

title: Bitchin' Rides: Road to the Ridler
subTitle: After almost a year of fabrication, the team starts assembling panels into the shape of a car. The chassis is also made of aluminium, and after a painstaking frame-design process, the two wild shapes are melded together for the first and last time.

title: Fast N' Loud
subTitle: The Monkeys race to finish the '68 Ford Galaxie XL before its owner comes to Dallas. Plus, the guys dig through barn grime to get to a '69 Camaro in Minnesota.

title: Seduced by Speed
subTitle: Jerry Wiegert builds a fighter jet he can drive in his super-fast super car, the Vector W8; the car turns heads wherever it goes, but after partnering with the son of a dictator, Wiegert's forced to fight to keep flying high.

title: Car Fix
subTitle: Fuller and Bumpus show what it takes to put a marine-grade LS7 into a classic '85 El Camino. There is a difference between engines built for the road and those built for the water.

title: Garage Squad
subTitle: The talented team restore a man's '69 Dodge Daytona. The owner is unwell, and fixing the car would be the perfect way to brighten his mood.
